{"id":"example","term":"Example","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Of Christ (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Peter 2:21\">1 Pet. 2:21</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 13:15\">John 13:15</a>); of pastors to their flocks (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Philippians 3:17\">Phil. 3:17</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Thessalonians 3:9\">2 Thess. 3:9</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Timothy 4:12\">1 Tim. 4:12</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Peter 5:3\">1 Pet. 5:3</a>); of the Jews as a warning (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Hebrews 4:11\">Heb. 4:11</a>); of the prophets as suffering affliction (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"James 5:10\">James 5:10</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Peter 2:21","John 13:15","Philippians 3:17","2 Thessalonians 3:9","1 Timothy 4:12","1 Peter 5:3","Hebrews 4:11","James 5:10"]}